text: Cotonopsis phuketensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Columbellidae, the dove snails. ==Description== The shell size varies between . ==Distribution== This species is distributed in the Andaman Sea along Thailand. ==References== Category:Columbellidae Category:Molluscs of the Indian Ocean Category:Gastropods described in 1998
